      "content": "Sure, let's break it down with a bit of a magical touch from our little friend, the wise old wizard of finance, who always knows how to make things grow. Imagine your $5,000 as the first seed planted in a fertile field, and every $300 you add is like watering it monthly. Over 30 years, that seed will grow into a mighty oak, thanks to the 7% annual return, which is like the sun and rain working together to help it flourish.\n\nNow, let's see how much of that oak tree is from your contributions and how much is from the magical interest earned by the wizard:\n\n1. **Your Contributions**: Over 30 years, you'll have added $300 x 12 months x 30 years = $108,000 directly to your account.\n\n2. **Interest Earned**: The rest of the growth is due to the wizard's magic. Using a magical savings calculator, we find that after 30 years, your account will have grown to approximately $1,066,000. Subtracting your contributions ($108,000) from this total gives us $958,000 in interest earned.\n\nSo, in this enchanted forest of finance, you've planted a seed and nurtured it",
